ENTRY            F0644   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0644001   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 11         23
TITLE      Measurement of the alpha particle decay width of the
           first 0+, T=2 state in 40Ca
AUTHOR     (S.K.B.Hesmondhalgh,E.F.Garman,D.M.Pringle,S.H.Chew,
           W.N.Catford,K.W.Allen)
INSTITUTE  (2UK OXF)
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,183,35,1987)
FACILITY   (VDGT,2UK OXF)
INC-SOURCE A 10 muA beam of 5.5 MeV He+ particles.
DETECTOR   (GELI)
           (SIBAR) Three silicon charged partial detectors.
           (NAICR) One gamma-ray detector was 12*15 cm NaI crystal
METHOD     (BCINT)
SAMPLE     The Oxford windowless cryo-pumped gas target was used.
           This target consists of a 9 cm long stainless
           steel tube with insulated nozzles at each end. Two
           litres of isotopically separated (99.6%) 36Ar were
           available for the experiments. The measurements were
           performed at a stabilized target pressure of
           13 Pa (100 um of Hg)of 36Ar.
ADD-RES    The elastic scattering data were analyzed with R-matrix
           theory.
HISTORY    (20040127C)
           (20251217A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              23
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        F0644002   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  4          7
REACTION   (18-AR-36(A,EL)18-AR-36,,DA,,REL)
           Data given in counts per incident particle (x 10E-14)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,S.K.B.Hesmondhalgh+,J,PL/B,183,35,1987) Fig.3
HISTORY    (20251217A) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR1 -> DATA-ERR.
           Values at col. DATA were multiplied by 1.E+14 as
           it is given on the figure.
ENDBIB               7
